.:: Puzzle 2x6-Level-4-3::.
The people use 6 different means of transport: tram, trike, airplane, skateboard, train, car
The people grow 6 different varities of flowers: daisy, azalea, dahlia, marigold, sunflower, rose
1. the person who growsdaisy is on the left of the person who growsdahlia##1
2. the person driving the airplane is on the left or right of the person who growsrose##3
3. the person who growsdahlia is on the left or right of the person driving the airplane##3
4. the person driving the skateboard is in an odd position##4
5. the person driving the car is on the left or right of the person driving the skateboard##3
6. the person driving the train is on the left or right of the person who growsdaisy##3
7. the person who growsazalea is on the left of the person driving the trike##1
8. the person who growsdaisy is on the far left or far right##3
9. the person who growsmarigold is the person driving the car##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |     1      |   2   |    3    |       4       |     5      |    6     |
| Transport   | tram    | train | airplane     | trike         | skateboard       | car     |
| Flower         | daisy | dahlia  | azalea | rose | sunflower | marigold |

